definition: to lure into a trap/to trap/to capture

sentences.english: Stores and warehouses should monitor populations with pheromone traps.
sentences.chinese: 仓储过程中应使用信息素诱捕器进行监测。

sentences.english: The scientists took the boric acid sweet bait to the West African nation of Mali.
sentences.chinese: 科学家将这种含糖硼酸诱捕剂带到了西非的马里。

sentences.english: Ensnared in maya, I am all but dead.
sentences.chinese: 在摩耶的诱捕下，我差点儿死去。

sentences.english: An intricate trap that entangles or ensnares its victim.
sentences.chinese: 缠上或诱捕它的牺牲品的复杂的捕捉机。

sentences.english: The team posed as drug dealers to trap the ringleaders.
sentences.chinese: 该队队员装扮成毒品贩子，诱捕罪犯头目。

sentences.english: It has been trapped for its valuable Brownish Black fur.
sentences.chinese: 常被诱捕以获取其贵重的浅棕黑色毛皮。

sentences.english: Stop Yoshino Kimura, he wanted to use Wang Chunlin Helen of Troy trap.
sentences.chinese: 吉野制止住木村，他想用王春林诱捕小龙女。

sentences.english: The long antenna-like stalks growing from the opee sea killer's head are actually lures that the beast uses to attract prey.
sentences.chinese: 奥皮海洋杀手运用头顶的长触须作为诱捕猎物的诱饵。

sentences.english: The police have been given extra powers to entrap drug traffickers.
sentences.chinese: 警方已经被进一步授权诱捕毒贩。

sentences.english: Entangling Roots and Ensnare work on Heroes again.
sentences.chinese: 树根缠绕和诱捕再次对英雄有效。

sentences.english: Brahman weeps, entrapped in the snare of the five elements.
sentences.chinese: 梵天被诱捕到五种元素的陷阱里，他哭泣着。

sentences.english: A fish trap utensil comprises a cage body equipped with 1 inverted barb or a plurality of inverted barbs.
sentences.chinese: 一种诱捕鱼的器具，一个笼体装配倒须1个至多个。

sentences.english: They sprayed it on plants near man-made ponds.
sentences.chinese: 他们将这种诱捕剂喷洒在人工池塘附近的植物上。

sentences.english: The hunters used nets to entrap the lion.
sentences.chinese: 猎人们以罗网诱捕狮子。

sentences.english: An enclosed place, such as a pond, into which wildfowl are lured for capture.
sentences.chinese: 围起来的地方，如池塘，可把野鸡诱捕在里面。

sentences.english: He used some cheese to trap the rat.
sentences.chinese: 他用了些乳酪诱捕耗子。

definition: to hunt and kill (an animal or fish)
to fish by casting a net/to capture/to surround and seize
to prey on/to catch and feed on/to hunt for food
to coerce (sb into doing sth bad)/to lure (into a trap)/to seduce
to hunt and arrest (fugitives)/to track down and arrest/a manhunt
to intercept/to cut off and capture
to shoot dead (with a gun, or bow and arrow)
